# This project does NOT use .env files for secrets.
# All secrets are stored in AWS SSM Parameter Store under /banyan/hasura/.
#
# Local development:
#   AWS_PROFILE=banyan bun run hasura:setup    # generates ddn/.env from SSM
#   AWS_PROFILE=banyan bun run hasura:tunnel   # SSM tunnel to RDS
#   bun run hasura:start                       # start local DDN dev server
#
# Deploy to DDN Cloud:
#   AWS_PROFILE=banyan bun run hasura:deploy   # fetches secrets, builds, deploys
#
# SSM parameters (/banyan/hasura/):
#
#   jwt-secret-key       — JWT HMAC HS256 key (SecureString)
#   ddn-connection-uri   — RDS connection via NLB for DDN Cloud (SecureString)
#   db-connection-uri    — Direct RDS connection for migrations (SecureString)
#   admin-token          — Pre-signed admin JWT (SecureString)
#   rds-nlb-endpoint     — NLB DNS name (String)
#   ddn-cloud-endpoint   — DDN Cloud GraphQL API URL (String)
#   apple-endpoint              — Apple subgraph GraphQL endpoint (SecureString)
#   apple-admin-secret          — Apple subgraph admin secret (SecureString)
#   phoenix-auth-service-url    — Phoenix auth service URL (String, default: https://oasis.papaya.asia)
